				<P><STRONG>CLASS:</STRONG>&nbsp;Shaman </P>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>On a scale of 1 (low) to 10 (high)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>HP:</STRONG> 10 - HP = Mana for Shaman, even at higher levels<BR><STRONG>Mana:</STRONG> 8&nbsp; - Mana is great as a base, but HP still replenishes it<BR><STRONG>Endurance:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>AC:</STRONG> 9 - Not getting hit when we inevitably draw aggro, or at least mitigating damage is very important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>HP Regen:</STRONG> 5<BR><STRONG>Mana Regen:</STRONG> 9<BR><STRONG>Endurance Regen:</STRONG> 1</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Strength:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Stamina:</STRONG> 10 - until cap, then falls behind (as does anything once capped)<BR><STRONG>Agility:</STRONG> 5<BR><STRONG>Dexterity:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Charisma:</STRONG> 10 - Charisma affects slow!!&nbsp; (I'M JOKING!!&nbsp; Really a 1 here)<BR><STRONG>Intelligence:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Wisdom:</STRONG> 10 - until cap, then falls behind (as does anything once capped)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Cold Resist:</STRONG> 8<BR><STRONG>Disease Resist:</STRONG> 8<BR><STRONG>Poison Resist:</STRONG> 8<BR><STRONG>Magic Resist:</STRONG> 8<BR><STRONG>Fire Resist:</STRONG> 8</DIV>
<DIV>*With all the prismatic/chromatic resists out there, all resists are equally important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Attack:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Delay:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Damage:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Range:</STRONG>&nbsp;1 - melee range;&nbsp; 10 - spell range</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Haste:</STRONG> 1</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Combat Effects:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Shielding:</STRONG> 8<BR><STRONG>Stun Resist:</STRONG> 10 - Can't land slow if you're stunned.&nbsp; And ogre ability doesn't stop spell stun.<BR><STRONG>Strikethrough:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>Spell Shield:</STRONG> 8<BR><STRONG>Avoidance:</STRONG> 6<BR><STRONG>Accuracy:</STRONG> 1<BR><STRONG>DOT Shielding:</STRONG> 7</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Skill Mods:</STRONG> 4 - Not really a benefit for shammies too much no matter how you look at it, other than maybe reduced fizzles<BR><STRONG>Click Effects:</STRONG> 7 - Well loved, esp for quick buffing, though getting current buffs on clickies is hard to do</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Proc Effects:</STRONG> 1 - fun, but not important</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Worn Effects:</STRONG> 3 - Faerune is important, after that, not much matters<BR><STRONG>Focus Effects:</STRONG> 10 - Absolutely a must.&nbsp; Shamen need every single focus effect out there practically, and juggling effects during upgrades can be&nbsp;a headache.</DIV>
				
